          <para styleclass="VariableName">Top-Tip:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="width:100%;">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Body Text">When there are many <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyads</text> in the model it is sometime not easy to see which <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text> whose closure you need to change.</para>
                <list id="8" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Interface2">Kinematics-Tree</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:normal;">: Click to Expand each </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Kinematic-Chain</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:normal;"> in the </text><text styleclass="Interface" style="font-style:normal;">Kinematics-Tree</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="font-style:normal;">&#32;</text></li>
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Interface2">Kinematics-Tree</text><text style="font-style:normal;">: Click each</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="Body Text">When you click to explore each dyad in the <text styleclass="Interface2">Kinematics-Tree</text>, the five elements in the Dyad (<text styleclass="VariableName">2 </text><text styleclass="Element">Parts</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> + 3 </text><text styleclass="Element">Joints</text>) become <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">red</text> in the graphic-area.</para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
